data.enText: to remove or get rid of sth/sb

data.chText: 有了信用卡就用不着携带很多现金。
data.enText: Credit cards eliminate the need to carry a lot of cash.

data.chText: 警方通过调查已经排除了两名嫌疑犯。
data.enText: The police have eliminated two suspects from their investigation.

data.chText: 这种饮食据称具有排除体内毒素的作用。
data.enText: This diet claims to eliminate toxins from the body.
to defeat a person or a team so that they no longer take part in a competition, etc.

data.chText: 所有英格兰队伍在比赛初期就被淘汰了。
data.enText: All the English teams were eliminated in the early stages of the competition.

data.chText: 消灭，干掉（尤指敌人或对手）
data.enText: to kill sb, especially an enemy or opponent

data.chText: 这个政权的左翼反对派多数已被除掉。
data.enText: Most of the regime's left-wing opponents were eliminated.

data.chText: 消除疾病 / 贫困 / 犯罪
比赛第一轮淘汰了三个队。
data.enText: There were three eliminations in the first round of the competition.
the elimination of toxins from the body

simple_means.memory_skill: e 出 + limin 限制 + ate 表动词 → 消除对事物的限制 → 消除

means: 消灭，干掉(尤指敌人或对手)

ex.chText: 他铲除了所有政治对手。
ex.enText: He eliminated all his political rivals.

ex.chText: 我们的目标是消除贫困。
ex.enText: Our goal is to eliminate poverty.

synonyms.bx: 通常指有步骤地除掉敌人、对手等或消除不需要的事物。

ex.chText: 林肯总统废除了美国的奴隶制。
ex.enText: President Lincoln abolished slavery in the United States.

synonyms.bx: 尤指正式废止旧时或不合理的法律、制度、习俗等。

ex.chText: 我们彻底消灭了入侵者。
这些炸弹只消一颗就能彻底毁灭像东京那么大的一座城市。
ex.enText: Just one of these bombs could annihilate a city the size of Tokyo.

synonyms.bx: 强调消灭或毁灭得非常彻底。

example: the plague wiped out an entire population
Let's eliminate the course on Akkadian hieroglyphics

tr: remove (an unknown variable) from two or more equations
dismiss from consideration or a contest
example: John was ruled out as a possible suspect because he had a strong alibi
This possibility can be eliminated from our consideration

tr: remove from a contest or race
example: The cyclist has eliminated all the competitors in the race

value.def: To eliminate something, especially something you do not want or need, means to remove it completely.

example.ex: The Sex Discrimination Act has not eliminated discrimination in employment...
example.tran: 《反性别歧视法》并未根除工作中的歧视。
纯理论研究院系即将被裁撤。

example.ex: If you think you may be allergic to a food or drink, eliminate it from your diet.
example.tran: 如果觉得可能对某种食物或饮料过敏，将其从日常饮食中去除。

value.tran: 消除，剔除，根除(尤指不需要之物)

example.ex: ...the prohibition and elimination of chemical weapons.
example.tran: 对化学武器的禁止和销毁

value.def: When a person or team is eliminated from a competition, they are defeated and so take no further part in the competition.

example.ex: I was eliminated from the 400 metres in the semi-finals...
example.tran: 我在400米半决赛中被淘汰。

example.ex: If you are eliminated in the show-jumping then you are out of the complete competition.
example.tran: 如果在马术障碍赛中被淘汰，就意味着完全出局。

value.def: If someone says that they have eliminated an enemy, they mean that they have killed them. By using the word 'eliminate', they are trying to make the action sound more positive than if they used the word 'kill'.

example.ex: He declared war on the government and urged right-wingers to eliminate their opponents...
example.tran: 他向政府宣战，并煽动右翼分子干掉他们的对手。

example.ex: The radio station claimed that 87,000 'reactionaries' had been eliminated.
example.tran: 广播电台声称已经消灭了87,000名“反动分子”。

trans: 扫盲；消除文盲；扫除文盲
